menu "breadboard: bb_health"

config BB_HEALTH_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register /api/health HTTP route via bb_registry"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_health self-registers GET /api/health through bb_registry.
        Disable to keep the bb_health_register_extender API but skip the route
        entirely.

config BB_HEALTH_STACK_POLL_MS
    int "Stack high-water monitor poll interval (ms)"
    default 10000
    range 1000 3600000
    help
        How often the stack high-water monitor checks all FreeRTOS task
        stack margins. Default 10 000 ms (10 s) is a low-overhead poll
        that catches margin erosion well before a real overflow.

        Note: the monitor requires CONFIG_FREERTOS_USE_TRACE_FACILITY=y
        (enabled automatically by FREERTOS_GENERATE_RUN_TIME_STATS or
        similar; check your sdkconfig). If TRACE_FACILITY is off, the
        monitor compiles as a no-op and this setting has no effect.

        Strongly recommended: also set
          CONFIG_FREERTOS_CHECK_STACKOVERFLOW_PTRVAL=y
        (CONFIG_FREERTOS_CHECK_STACKOVERFLOW=2) so a real overflow prints
        an attributable task-name message instead of a silent abort.

config BB_HEALTH_STACK_LOW_BYTES
    int "Stack low-water threshold (bytes)"
    default 512
    range 64 65536
    help
        Free stack bytes below which a task is flagged as low. The monitor
        posts a health.stack event on the first poll where a task crosses
        below this threshold (transition into low), not on every poll, to
        avoid spamming the event bus.

        uxTaskGetStackHighWaterMark returns words; the monitor multiplies
        by sizeof(StackType_t) (4 on Xtensa/RISC-V 32-bit) to get bytes.

config BB_HEALTH_AUTO_ATTACH
    bool "Auto-attach health.stack to /api/events"
    default y
    depends on BB_EVENT_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    help
        When enabled, bb_health's stack monitor attaches the "health.stack"
        topic to the bb_event_routes SSE stream so /api/events surfaces it
        without an explicit consumer call. Disable if you want the bb_event
        topic for internal subscribers only.

endmenu
